\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Professional and documented communication is foundational to service accountability,
 operational continuity,
 and public trust.
 The standards defined in this section ensure that all service-related interactions conducted by Information Operations personnel —
 regardless of channel or audience —
 are traceable,
 appropriately scoped,
 and consistent with the Department's governance obligations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Required Communication Channels
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The designated work order system is the authoritative channel for all service requests,
 technical communications,
 and service lifecycle documentation.
 Work order records are subject to the retention obligations established in NRS 239.125 (Local Government Records Management Program) and NAC 239.155 (Retention and Disposition of Local Government Records).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Channel Mandate
\series default
:
 Unless the designated work order system is inaccessible due to a documented system outage,
 All Information Operations Personnel shall initiate,
 track,
 and close all service requests and IT responses within the designated work order system.
 Channel exceptions require justification documented in the relevant work order.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Out-of-Band Summarization
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall summarize verbal or informal communications —
 including hallway conversations,
 phone calls,
 and instant messages —
 and enter the summary into the relevant work order within one (1) business day of the interaction,
 or prior to ticket closure,
 whichever occurs first.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Private Notes Use
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall default to standard,
 user-visible notes for all ticket documentation and shall use Private Notes only for the following authorized purposes:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Documenting internal security vulnerabilities or unpatched exploit data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Redacting or handling accidental spillage of PII,
 PHI,
 or CJI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Documenting personnel-sensitive actions such as HR-directed account lockouts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Internal technical diagnostics that would not be meaningful for the end user.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 Private Notes remain subject to applicable retention obligations and public records law.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Vendor and External Partner Communications
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall summarize communications with vendors or external partners in the relevant work order or project record within one (1) business day.
 Where such communications occur outside the designated work order system,
 the summary shall document the substance of those communications.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Documentation Substitution
\series default
:
 When an approved exception to this policy precludes full documentation,
 the authorized Information Operations Personnel shall summarize the exception using Private Notes in accordance with the constraints defined above and within one (1) business day.
 Where the sensitive nature of an exception precludes narrative documentation,
 the authorized Information Operations Personnel shall generate a placeholder record in the designated work order system referencing the authorized exception without disclosing the sensitive content.
\end_layout

